By: Rûmi
---
\'Tis as when a bird is perched on your head, and your soul trembles
for fear of its flitting.

So you dare not stir from your place, lest your beautiful bird should
take to the air：

You dare not breathe, you suppress a cough, lest that humâ should fly
away.
